The paper deals with improving the quality of images obtained through computational ghost imaging using deep learning. This involves image processing and computer vision techniques, which are typically covered under the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the paper also deals with the issue of noise reduction, which is a common problem in signal processing and information theory, and hence could be classified under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves the use of deep neural networks, which is a popular area of research in artificial intelligence, and hence could be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, which could be classified under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper could also be classified under cs.OH (Other Computer Science), as it involves a combination of different areas of computer science.
